    <section id="projects" class="card">
        <h2>Projects</h2>
        <p>In his first year of graduate studies, Du Shuo participated in an event triggered control project using traditional TCP methods. The stability analysis of the final closed-loop system is simulated as a nonlinear impulse dynamic system, and the Lyapunov method is extended to prove the boundedness of the system state and the estimation error of neural network weights.</p>
